{{Infobox award | name = Prix Versailles | description = stores, hotels and restaurants architectures around the world | current_awards = | presenter = World Prix Versailles Organization | year = 2015 | website = {{url|prix-versailles.com}} }}
The '''Prix Versailles''' is an annual award dedicated to commercial architecture which was inaugurated in 2015. Discerned at the headquarters of the [[UNESCO|United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization (UNESCO)]] in Paris, it encompasses several categories, with the winners being selected by an independent judges panel. It is the world architecture award for stores, hotels and restaurants.<ref>[http://diversum.net/fichiers/File/%28fr%29_Prix_Versailles_21-04-2016.pdf {{fr}} Press release from 21 April 2016] (accessed on 24 August 2016)</ref>
==Purpose and process== Following a call for submissions, this award singles out the architects and owners of shops and stores, hotels and restaurants around the world that are found to be particularly remarkable, from a perspective of their exterior architecture and their interior design. The prix focuses on commercial buildings, with the clear aim of fostering a better mix of the economic and cultural sectors.<ref>[http://diversum.net/fichiers/File/%28en%29_Prix_Versailles_30-05-2016.pdf Press release from 30 May 2016] (accessed on 24 August 2016)</ref> [[Irina Bokova]], Director-General of [[UNESCO]], declared on 19 June 2015, "The Prix Versailles is one of the ways to shine light on the intersection between creation, art and economics".<ref>[http://diversum.net/fichiers/File/%28en%29_Prix_Versailles_22-06-2015.pdf Press release from 22 June 2015] (accessed on 24 August 2016)</ref>
==Judges== The judges panel includes the following members:
