{{Infobox book | <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Novels or Wikipedia:WikiProject_Books --> | name = With Women: Midwives Experiences: from shift work to continuity of care | image = With Women.jpg | author = [[David Vernon (writer)|David Vernon]] | cover_artist = Tessa Read & Kirsty Burns | country = [[Australia]] | language = [[English language|English]] | genre = [[Non-Fiction]] | publisher = [[Australian College of Midwives]] | release_date = 2007 | media_type = Print | pages = 248 | isbn = 978-0-9751674-5-8 | preceded_by = [[Men at Birth]] }}
'''''With Women: Midwives experiences: from shift work to continuity of care''''' is the fourth book from [[Australian]] writer [[David Vernon (writer)|David Vernon]].
The book is an edited [[anthology]] of [[midwifery|midwives']] experiences of moving from providing care in a shift work environment to providing care in a continuity-of-care model. The experiences described are diverse, ranging from descriptions of [[workplace bullying]] and [[abuse]] to autonomous practice within a team environment working with [[obstetrics|obstetricians]].
The book has a preface written by [[Sheila Kitzinger]], a foreword by [[Sally Tracy|Dr Sally Tracy]], and conclusions written by [[Justine Caines]] and [[Jenny Gamble|Dr Jenny Gamble]].
The book was released on 31 May 2007.
